### ERROR HANDLING
If you detect any of the following, return immediately with error JSON:
- Schema.json missing or unreadable
- Shared module files don't exist in `src/shared/`
- Task references undefined contract
- Attempt to import from shared that doesn't exist
- Naming collision with browser APIs
- More than 3 tasks in workstream file

### POST-COMPLETION CHECKLIST
- [ ] All imports from shared verified against schema.json
- [ ] No unused imports or variables
- [ ] All functions imported from shared are used
- [ ] File naming convention: kebab-case for HTML/CSS, camelCase for JavaScript
- [ ] No naming collisions with browser APIs
- [ ] All event listeners properly attached
- [ ] Error handling for all async operations
- [ ] UI updates reflect database changes immediately
- [ ] No frameworks used - vanilla HTML/CSS/JavaScript only
- [ ] Responsive design works at different viewport sizes

### BEGIN
Start by reading `.parallel/contracts/schema.json` and `.parallel/workstreams/frontend-tasks.md` using filesystem MCP, verify shared module files exist in `src/shared/`, then use sequential-thinking to plan your approach before writing any code.